Flat 2D surfaces curved in 3D¶

In this document we test the benefits of using multi-time-steps Markov transition matrix as inputs to the KL divergence optimization solved by t-SNE. When constructing a proximity matrix for t-SNE, one might consider keeping bandwidths small for the Gaussian kernel, but then taking higher powers, $P^T$, of the corresponding conditional probability matrix, $P = P_{j|i}$. Varying powers of $P$ allow for studing the geometry of the data at different scales.

1.2 Visualization with t-SNE¶

First, we compute the standard t-SNE embedding, withing FIt-SNE implementation (fastest). Then, we modify the computed transition (conditional) probability matrix by taking its powers, and recompute the embeddings to see if it improves.

1.2.1 Standard t-SNE¶

ncopies = 10
perps  = [5, 10, 25, 50, 100, 250]
def standard_tsne(X, perp, seed):
    cwd = os.getcwd()
    it_dir = './swissroll_res/fitsne/perp'+ str(perp) + \
        '_it' + str(seed) + "/"
    os.makedirs(it_dir)
    os.chdir(it_dir)
    start = time.time()
    Y = fast_tsne(X, perplexity=perp, seed=seed,
                  nthreads=3,data_path= 'data.dat',
                 result_path = 'result.dat')
    end = time.time()
    res = {'embedding' : Y, 'time' : end - start, 'seed' : seed, 
           'perp' : perp, 'method' : 'standard_fitsne'}
    os.chdir(cwd)
    return res

results = {}
pool = mp.Pool(processes = min(len(perps)*ncopies, mp.cpu_count()))
for perp in perps:
    for i in range(ncopies):
        seed = np.random.randint(1, 1e5, size = 1)[0]
        #print('Perplexity: %d, copy %d' %(perp, seed))
        trial = 'perp' + str(perp) + '_it' + str(i)
        results[trial] = pool.apply_async(standard_tsne, args = (X, perp, seed))
pool.close()
pool.join()
fitsne_res = {name : result.get() for name, result in results.items()}

def get_res(res_dict, label, perps, tsteps=None, figsize = (15, 15)):
    embd_time = {name : out['time'] for name, out in res_dict.items()}
    embd = {name : out['embedding'] for name, out in res_dict.items()}     
    # Plot examples:
    items2plot = []
    for perp in perps:
        if tsteps is not None:
            for tstep in tsteps:
                iperp = 'perp' + str(perp) + '_tstep' + str(tstep)
                iembd = [x for x in res_dict.keys() if iperp in x]
                items2plot += [iembd[0]]

        else:
            iperp = 'perp' + str(perp) + "_"
            iembd = [x for x in res_dict.keys() if iperp in x]
            items2plot += iembd[0:min(5, len(iembd))]
    names2plot = []        
    for i in range(len(items2plot)):
        name = updated_name = items2plot[i]
        if tsteps is not None: updated_name = name.split("_it")[0]
        name = "%s (%d sec)" %(updated_name, embd_time[name])
        names2plot.append(name)
    emd2plot = [embd[name] for name in items2plot]
    p = plot_embdeddings(emd2plot, color=label, 
                         name_lst=names2plot, figsize=figsize, 
                         s = 10, edgecolor='black', linewidth=0.1)
    return embd, embd_time

1.2.2. Diffusion t-SNE¶

In [7]:
def diffusion_tsne(X, perp, tstep, seed):
    it_dir = './swissroll_res/difftsne/perp'+ str(perp) + \
        '_t' + str(tstep) + '_it' + str(seed) + "/"
    start = time.time()
    resBeta = beta_to_Pt(X, perplexity = perp, beta = None, time_step = tstep, 
                         thresh = 1e-16, save = True, save_dir=it_dir)
    time1 = time.time()
    Y = fast_tsne(X, seed=seed, load_affinities = 'load', 
                  affinities_dir = it_dir, save_files= True, nthreads=3)
    end = time.time()
    res = {'embedding' : Y, 'perp' : perp, 'tstep': tstep, 
           'method' : 'diffusion_fitsne', 'seed' : seed,
           'time1' : time1 - start, 'time2' : end - time1,
           'time' : end - start}
    return res

ncopies = 10
perps  = [5, 10, 25, 50] 
tsteps  = [1, 5, 10, 20, 50]
nComb = len(tsteps) * ncopies

difftsne_res_dict = {}
for perp in perps:
    pool = mp.Pool(processes = min(nComb, mp.cpu_count()))
    results = {}
    for tstep in tsteps: 
        print('Perplexity: %d, t-step %d' %(perp, tstep))
        for i in range(ncopies):
            seed = np.random.randint(1, 1e5, size = 1)[0]
            trial = 'perp' + str(perp) + '_tstep' + str(tstep) +'_it' + str(i)
            try:
                results[trial] = pool.apply_async(
                    diffusion_tsne, args = (X, perp, tstep, seed))
            except:
                results[trial] = {'embedding' : -1, 'time': -1}
    pool.close()
    pool.join()
    res = {name : result.get() for name, result in results.items()}
    difftsne_res_dict['perp' + str(perp)] = res

def diffusion_tsne(X, perp, tstep, seed):
    it_dir = './swissroll_res/difftsne/perp'+ str(perp) + \
        '_t' + str(tstep) + '_it' + str(seed) + "/"
    start = time.time()
    resBeta = beta_to_Pt(X, perplexity = perp, beta = None, time_step = tstep, 
                         thresh = 1e-16, save = True, save_dir=it_dir)
    time1 = time.time()
    Y = fast_tsne(X, seed=seed, load_affinities = 'load', 
                  affinities_dir = it_dir, save_files= True, nthreads=3)
    end = time.time()
    res = {'embedding' : Y, 'perp' : perp, 'tstep': tstep, 
           'method' : 'diffusion_fitsne', 'seed' : seed,
           'time1' : time1 - start, 'time2' : end - time1,
           'time' : end - start}
    return res

ncopies = 10
perps  = [5, 10, 25, 50] 
tsteps  = [1, 5, 10, 20, 50]
nComb = len(tsteps) * ncopies

scaled_difftsne_res_dict = {}
for perp in perps:
    pool = mp.Pool(processes = min(nComb, mp.cpu_count()))
    results = {}
    for tstep in tsteps: 
        print('Perplexity: %d, t-step %d' %(perp, tstep))
        for i in range(ncopies):
            seed = np.random.randint(1, 1e5, size = 1)[0]
            trial = 'perp' + str(perp) + '_tstep' + str(tstep) +'_it' + str(i)
            try:
                results[trial] = pool.apply_async(
                    diffusion_tsne, args = (X, perp, tstep, seed))
            except:
                results[trial] = {'embedding' : -1, 'time': -1}
    pool.close()
    pool.join()
    res = {name : result.get() for name, result in results.items()}
    scaled_difftsne_res_dict['perp' + str(perp)] = res
